announcements.title: Watch the Google I/O keynotes and session videos
announcements.summary: Videos continue to be posted on the site, so keep checking back for updates!

announcements.title: Introducing Google Analytics app for Android
announcements.summary: Google Analytics app for Android enables users to access their Analytics accounts on the go with reports optimized for mobile devices.

announcements.title: Help translate the amazing Google Glass demo into your language
Announcing Mobile App Analytics
announcements.summary: Mobile App Analytics helps app developers and marketers measure the end-to-end engagement and value of their mobile apps.

announcements.title: Avoid heading back to your hotel too early by checking out some of our Community Events taking place tonight
Enhancements to Styled Maps added to Google Maps API
announcements.summary: The latest version of the Google Maps API (v. 3) is launching an explicit color styler and extending its set of element selectors to provide finer grained control over how features are restyled.

announcements.title: Day 1 keynote video is live on YouTube
announcements.summary: Watch it again, or see it for the first time.

announcements.title: Google Play update, new developer tools
announcements.summary: Google Play app now offers movies and shows, new developer tools available for Google TV.

announcements.title: Chrome makes updates to Apps ecosystem
announcements.summary: Further enhancements to our apps platform for Chrome, evolving packaged apps architecture with improved capabilities, enhanced offline mode, and new access points.

announcements.title: Google+ Platform for Mobile
announcements.summary: Announcing the Google+ platform for mobile, including SDKs for Android and iOS (available soon), and mobile web optimized social plugins (available now).

announcements.title: Heat Maps and Symbols added to Google Maps API
announcements.summary: The latest version of the Google Maps API (v. 3) offers improved data visualization and interactivity for developers with the additions of Heat Maps and Symbols.

announcements.title: New sessions from Chrome & Cloud Platform have just gone live to the schedule.
Sergey Brin and the jumpers redux!
announcements.summary: Today we're on the roof of Moscone Center with Sergey watching from behind the scenes. Another great jump live in a Google+ Hangout via Google Glass.

announcements.title: New Web platform innovations: Google and Cirque du Soleil
announcements.summary: A collaboration between Google and Cirque du Soleil shows off a host of new web platform capabilities that wouldn’t have been possible a year ago.

announcements.title: Google Compute Engine launches
announcements.summary: Google's VM offering, Google Compute Engine, launches to limited preview.

announcements.title: Chromebooks on sale at Best Buy in the U.S.
announcements.summary: For those who want to try the Chromebook first-hand, we’re expanding the Chrome Zone experience centers to include select Best Buy stores around the U.S.

announcements.title: Google Docs Offline
announcements.summary: Now access Google Docs offline from any device.

announcements.title: Google Drive for iOS
announcements.summary: Google Drive is now available for your iPhone, iPad, and iPod Touch.

announcements.title: Watch the Chrome Keynote on YouTube
announcements.summary: An alternate link for your viewing pleasure

announcements.title: Chrome for iOS
announcements.summary: Chrome is now available for your iPhone, iPad, and iPod Touch.

announcements.title: Chrome for Android moves to Stable
announcements.summary: Chrome for Android is moving out of Beta to Stable.

announcements.title: Chrome now has 310M active users worldwide
announcements.summary: Up from 160M users announced at last year's Google I/O.

announcements.title: Hello to I/O Live and I/O Extended participants around the world
announcements.summary: The keynote will begin in 15 minutes.

announcements.title: Welcome to Google I/O, Day 2
announcements.summary: Join us for today's keynote at 10 AM PDT.

announcements.title: Whew! Time to put those laptops down.
announcements.summary: Learning's done for the day. We're heading to After Hours!

announcements.title: Gestures in Android
announcements.summary: Introducing 16 new gestures in Android to help users quickly use apps and controls without looking at the screen.

announcements.title: In-App Payments: new pricing and subscription options for integrating Google Wallet
announcements.summary: Announcing a new, industry-leading pricing model and introducing the recurring subscriptions feature.

announcements.title: New YouTube Mobile Android App
announcements.summary: Bringing your channel guide to YouTube Mobile on Android, and making playback faster on the go.

announcements.title: Apps Script updates
announcements.summary: Updates include a new standalone editor for creating, editing and publishing scripts; the ability to create and store scripts in Google Drive; and the ability to distribute scripts as web apps in the Chrome Web Store.

announcements.title: Google App Engine offers EU datastores
announcements.summary: EU datastores are now available for Premier Google App Engine customers.

announcements.title: New and updated YouTube APIs
announcements.summary: New APIs for YouTube Analytics, updated data, API and more.

announcements.title: Public transit data included in Google Maps API
announcements.summary: Google Maps API now enables developers to add transit data, including public transit directions, to their maps and apps.

announcements.title: Launch of new 3D imagery on Google Earth for Android
announcements.summary: New 3D imagery - complete with 3D  buildings, terrain and landscaping - will be available for select metropolitan areas on Google Earth for Android.

announcements.title: New Hangout App Metrics
announcements.summary:
In the 90 days since we launched apps in hangouts, we’ve seen:
over 200 hangout apps, average duration of a hangout increase by 2.5x when participants use an app, 1 in 3 hangouts use an app, partners like Cacoo doubling their user base after launch.

announcements.title: New Hangout Apps
announcements.summary: Introducing a new set of featured apps for Google+ Hangouts.

announcements.title: You're invited to the first Google+ Event
announcements.summary: Google I/O After Hours is tonight and you're on the guest list! To get into full Party Mode, just download the latest Google+ app and RSVP to the event. We'll see you tonight!

announcements.title: Offline Maps for Android
announcements.summary: Offline Maps for Android enables users to access Google Maps without a data connection. Great for traveling!

announcements.title: Don't miss new sessions just added to today's schedule.
announcements.summary: Check signs at Moscone, the I/O mobile app, or website for the latest updates from Android, Chrome, Cloud Platform, Commerce, Google Drive and Google+.

announcements.title: Introducing Version 2 of the Google Drive SDK
announcements.summary: Updated APIs and other tools to make it easier for developers to build apps that integrate seamlessly with Drive on the web and mobile devices.

announcements.title: Google+ Events
announcements.summary: Introducing Google+ Events, a new way to create, capture, and share public and private events -- before, during, and after they take place.

announcements.title: Sergey Brin and friends demo Project Glass - from the air!
announcements.summary: Jumping out of a Zeppelin, wearing Google Glass units, live in a Hangout IN Air!

announcements.title: Android and iOS Google+ tablet apps
announcements.summary: Announcing the first Google+ apps designed with Android and iOS tablets in mind.

announcements.title: Nexus Q
announcements.summary: The best way to enjoy Google Play at home.

announcements.summary: Purchase it direct, straight from Google Play, with orders shipping mid-July.

announcements.title: The Playground is open
announcements.summary: A new update to Android, the first tablet from Google, and the first ever social-streaming device.

announcements.title: Nexus 7: The first tablet from Google
announcements.summary: Super powerful, super portable.

announcements.title: More of the entertainment you love, on Google Play
announcements.summary: Now offering magazines, TV shows, and movies for sale.

announcements.title: Google Play is growing exponentially
announcements.summary: 20 billion apps have been downloaded, and that number is growing by more than one billion every month.
